               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Dānish nāmah-'i jahān by Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn ʿAlī Amīrān al-Ḥusaynī al-Iṣfahānī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/gf2014026092 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005357" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_800-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656436.0x000001 viaf_181760170">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn ʿAlī Amīrān al-Ḥusaynī al-Iṣfahānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_181760170">غياث الدّين على ابن على اميران الحسينى الاصفهانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3">Dānish nāmah-'i jahān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3">دانش نامهٴ جهان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Encyclopaedia of sciences, entitled 
                <title key="work_3">Dānish nāmah-'i jahān</title>, written by Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn ʿAlī Amīrān al-Ḥusaynī al-Iṣfahānī (d. 606/1209-10).
                        </p>
                        <p>The treatise is divided into ten sections termed faṣl, with further subdivisions, and concluding with a khātimah.</p>
                        <p>Spaces allotted for diagrams have been left blank throughout.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 116v): completed at 
                <placeName>Patna</placeName>, Tuesday (?), 4 Rabīʿ al-Avval 1025/22 March 1616.
                        </p>
                        <p>Neat scribal nastaʿlīq occasionally tending to shikastah.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
